SIMPLE: fortieth
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fortieth
<hw>For"ti*eth</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>fe⟦oacute⟧wertigo<?/a</ets>. See <er>Forty</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Following the thirty-ninth, or preceded by thirty-nine units,
things, or parts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Constituting one of forty equal parts into which
anything is divided.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fortieth</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Fortieth
<hw>For"ti*eth</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One of forty equal parts into
which one whole is divided; the quotient of a unit divided by forty; one
next in order after the thirty-ninth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fortifiable</ent>⟦br⟧
